<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871007-0005 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Funtime Inc.</HL><DD> 10/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FNTMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Funtime Inc., Cleveland, said a management-led group offered $7 a share to acquire the company.    The leveraged buy-out proposal has the backing of The Ohio Co., a Columbus-based investment banker that owns a majority of Funtime's approximately 3.3 million shares outstanding. Funtime, which owns amusement parks and restaurants, said its board will submit the proposal at a special shareholder meeting.    The transaction has a total value of $63 million, including the assumption of debt by the investment group, the group said.    The group includes Dale W. Van Voorhis, president of Funtime; Gasper C. Lococo, executive vice president of Funtime, and Bruce C. Walborn, chief executive of Mills Hall Walborn, a Cleveland public relations and advertising firm.    Funtime said Kidder, Peabody andamp; Co. arranged the financing for the transaction and that Heller Financial Inc. and Guarantee Security Life Insurance Co., a unit of Transmark USA Inc., committed financing, subject to certain conditions. </TEXT></DOC>